revision.text:
{{Infobox artwork | image_file=Tom Roberts-Allegro con brio, Bourke Street west c 1885-86.jpg | backcolor=#FBF5DF | painting_alignment=right | image_size=300px | title=Bourke Street (Allegro con brio) | artist=[[Tom Roberts]] | year=[[1886 in art|1886]] | type=oil on canvas on composition board | height_metric=51.2 | width_metric=76.7 | height_imperial= | width_imperial= | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[Canberra]] | museum=[[National Gallery of Australia]] }} '''''Bourke Street''''' is a [[1886 in art|1886]] painting by Australian artist [[Tom Roberts]]. Roberts originally titled the work '''''Allegro con brio'''''.<ref name="NLA">{{cite web|title= Bourke Street, Melbourne (picture) / Tom Roberts. |url=http://www.nla.gov.au/apps/cdview?pi=nla.pic-an2268340&fullrecord=yes|work=Digital collections|publisher=National Library of Australia|accessdate=19 October 2010}}</ref> The painting depicts the western end of [[Bourke Street, Melbourne|Bourke Street]], one of the main thoroughfares in [[Melbourne]] as seen from the [[Buckley & Nunn]] drapery.<ref name="EMelbourne">{{cite web|last=Spate|first=Virginia|title=Bourke Street (Tom Roberts)|url=http://www.emelbourne.net.au/biogs/EM00220b.htm|work=EMelbourne|publisher=University of Melbourne}}</ref>
The work was painted a few months after Roberts' return to Australia in 1885, after he had spent four years in Europe .<ref name=EMelbourne /> It was not displayed until 1890, and only five days beforehand, Roberts added three female figures to the lower left.<ref name=EMelbourne /><ref name="McQueen">{{cite web|last=McQueen|first=Humphrey|title=Allegro con brio, Bourke Street west|url=http://home.alphalink.com.au/~loge27/roberts/roberts_allegro.htm|accessdate=19 October 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110309125644/http://home.alphalink.com.au/~loge27/roberts/roberts_allegro.htm|archivedate=9 March 2011|df=}}</ref> Roberts was unable to find a buyer and handed the painting to fellow artist, [[Frederick McCubbin]]. In 1920, McCubbin's widow sold the painting to the [[Commonwealth Parliamentary Library]] for 20 [[Guinea (British coin)|guineas]]&mdash;forwarding the proceeds to Roberts, who was in London at the time.<ref name=McQueen />
