{{Infobox building |name= '''Hong Kong Visual Arts Center''' |image= Hong Kong Visual Arts Center.JPG |alt= |caption= |start_date= |opened_date= 1992 |location= |map_type= |map_alt= |map_caption= |coordinates = |native_name= |alternate_names= |cost= |website= |floor_count= |floor_area= |roof= |top_floor= |awards= |architect = |main_contractor= |structural_engineer= |references= }}
[[File:Apartment Blocks in Mid-levels (cropped).jpg|thumb|Side view of Hong Kong Visual Arts Centre, with [[St. Joseph's College, Hong Kong|St. Joseph's College]] in the background.]] [[File:Side view of Hong Kong Visual Arts Centre.JPG|thumb|Side view of Hong Kong Visual Arts Centre (A view from Hong Kong Park)]] The '''Hong Kong Visual Arts Centre''' ({{zh|t=香港視覺藝術中心}}) is located in [[Hong Kong Park]], at 7A [[Kennedy Road, Hong Kong|Kennedy Road]] in [[Central, Hong Kong|Central]], [[Hong Kong Island]], [[Hong Kong]]. It was opened by Leung Ding-Bong, then chairman of the [[Urban Council]], in 1992.
The centre encourages local art creation. It was restructured from an early 20th-century building called Cassels Block, a former barracks for married British officers of [[Victoria Barracks, Hong Kong|Victoria Barracks]]. It currently provides an area and facilities for local artists. It includes modern artefacts and sculptures.
The historic building is listed as a [[List of Grade II historic buildings in Hong Kong|Grade II historic building]].<ref>[http://www.amo.gov.hk/form/historical.pdf List of Graded Historic buildings in Hong Kong (As at 6 Jan 2007)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110709224215/http://www.amo.gov.hk/form/historical.pdf |date=2011-07-09 }}</ref> {{Coord|22.27680|114.15933|display=title}}
